{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"62ae1241-91ac-498b-be88-342bb4dc0dbd","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report skipped tests in the test results with the reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"76ed5e73-9fb9-4e4e-bb94-235b477cc9bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide this from my knowledge.","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"1BC3:1BD824:BBEC08:D4EBB0:6A03D24C"},"id":"a5ef5b82-72e1-433e-9226-c91e8397c724","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:22:26.542Z","parentId":"6fb88a8a-4386-4416-a9d1-17232ae03c68"}
